1
00:00:13,540 --> 00:00:15,780
♪Trap my frame♪

2
00:00:15,980 --> 00:00:20,060
♪Plagues demand I bow in shame♪

3
00:00:20,780 --> 00:00:22,940
♪Snare my soul♪

4
00:00:23,020 --> 00:00:27,100
♪Rules command I swallow my pride♪

5
00:00:27,260 --> 00:00:30,620
♪Mock my way♪

6
00:00:30,900 --> 00:00:34,060
♪Chained me where I must stay♪

7
00:00:34,420 --> 00:00:36,780
♪Taught me to kneel, not to speak♪

8
00:00:37,020 --> 00:00:41,220
♪And to let my life pass by in silence♪

9
00:00:42,100 --> 00:00:44,100
♪But I heard the wind♪

10
00:00:44,220 --> 00:00:45,900
♪From the sea and the sky♪

11
00:00:46,180 --> 00:00:47,660
♪It said don't bend♪

12
00:00:47,780 --> 00:00:49,820
♪Bow your head, and your chains begin♪

13
00:00:49,940 --> 00:00:51,380
♪You are the wave♪

14
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:53,300
♪And the wind that won't behave♪

15
00:00:53,380 --> 00:00:56,340
♪How could you be chained?♪

16
00:00:56,740 --> 00:00:58,740
♪Untamed, uncaged, unclaimed♪

17
00:00:58,780 --> 00:01:00,540
♪You're the blade in my gaze♪

18
00:01:00,620 --> 00:01:02,420
♪This world will leave you no space♪

19
00:01:02,500 --> 00:01:04,220
♪Then pierce it with your blaze♪

20
00:01:04,220 --> 00:01:06,100
♪My silent grind♪

21
00:01:06,100 --> 00:01:08,060
♪My aching pain♪

22
00:01:08,060 --> 00:01:10,300
♪Will one day turn...♪

23
00:01:11,860 --> 00:01:14,620
♪I am who I am♪

24
00:01:14,620 --> 00:01:18,140
♪My greatest ambition♪

25
00:01:18,220 --> 00:01:21,300
♪If the world can't contain me♪

26
00:01:21,380 --> 00:01:24,940
♪Then I'll break through it♪

27
00:01:25,420 --> 00:01:26,940
♪Become who I am♪

28
00:01:26,940 --> 00:01:28,260
[Wild Ambition Bloom]

29
00:01:28,260 --> 00:01:29,980
[Adapted from Stone and Water's novel,
The Uncaged Flame]

30
00:01:29,980 --> 00:01:32,980
[Episode 36]

31
00:01:34,150 --> 00:01:35,850
What about our branches?

32
00:01:36,230 --> 00:01:37,410
Some were set ablaze,

33
00:01:38,560 --> 00:01:39,410
some seized by force,

34
00:01:40,920 --> 00:01:42,100
some sealed off,

35
00:01:42,590 --> 00:01:44,490
and the rest plundered clean.

36
00:01:47,790 --> 00:01:49,260
What about
the original Shouyuan Apothecary?

37
00:01:50,070 --> 00:01:50,820
It

38
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:53,180
was also sealed shut.

39
00:01:55,230 --> 00:01:56,130
What about

40
00:01:56,150 --> 00:01:57,460
its other branches nationwide?

41
00:01:58,430 --> 00:01:59,130
Gone.

42
00:02:00,790 --> 00:02:05,020
All shops in north and northeast China
fell.

43
00:02:06,510 --> 00:02:07,850
All our decades of efforts

44
00:02:08,120 --> 00:02:09,220
amount to nothing?

45
00:02:10,840 --> 00:02:11,940
What about Qizhou herb market?

46
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:14,340
It

47
00:02:15,840 --> 00:02:17,380
has also gone.

48
00:02:18,710 --> 00:02:20,730
How to do business now?

49
00:02:36,360 --> 00:02:37,680
[Ma Juncai]

50
00:02:39,470 --> 00:02:41,060
Mr. Ma, welcome.

51
00:02:41,310 --> 00:02:42,220
What can we do for you?

52
00:02:42,360 --> 00:02:44,690
On behalf of the National Government,

53
00:02:44,710 --> 00:02:47,260
I'm here to discuss
a great cause with you.

54
00:02:48,240 --> 00:02:49,340
I'm all ears.

55
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:53,610
Since founding Shaohua Pharmaceuticals,

56
00:02:53,630 --> 00:02:54,780
you've achieved remarkably.

57
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:56,540
Your innovations in all aspects

58
00:02:56,560 --> 00:02:58,060
align with

59
00:02:58,080 --> 00:03:00,890
Civil-Economic Construction Movement

60
00:03:01,030 --> 00:03:02,130
proposed by Mr. Chiang.

61
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:05,570
So the National Government wishes

62
00:03:05,590 --> 00:03:06,660
to build factories with you,

63
00:03:07,400 --> 00:03:11,780
to rescue the economy
teetering on collapse

64
00:03:12,080 --> 00:03:12,940
and to secure

65
00:03:13,150 --> 00:03:16,730
prosperous livelihoods for its people.

66
00:03:18,470 --> 00:03:20,940
How would this collaboration work?

67
00:03:22,910 --> 00:03:25,890
The National Government will cover

68
00:03:26,080 --> 00:03:28,130
all costs and operational logistics.

69
00:03:28,560 --> 00:03:32,060
You'll invest with the formula

70
00:03:32,280 --> 00:03:33,260
for the Miracle Pill.

71
00:03:37,840 --> 00:03:39,690
What's her percentage of shares?

72
00:03:39,840 --> 00:03:40,610
Ten percent.

73
00:03:40,630 --> 00:03:41,220
Ten percent?

74
00:03:41,240 --> 00:03:41,980
Precisely.

75
00:03:43,310 --> 00:03:45,060
Who's the owner of the formula?

76
00:03:46,680 --> 00:03:48,340
Since this is a joint venture,

77
00:03:48,630 --> 00:03:51,850
the National Government and Ms. Chu

78
00:03:51,870 --> 00:03:52,730
will be the co-owners.

79
00:03:56,360 --> 00:03:56,980
Mr. Ma,

80
00:03:57,750 --> 00:03:58,980
according to international practice,

81
00:03:59,240 --> 00:04:00,820
if Ms. Chu makes a technology investment

82
00:04:01,280 --> 00:04:03,060
with a product like the Miracle Pill,

83
00:04:03,150 --> 00:04:05,130
she shall receive at least 50% shares.

84
00:04:06,360 --> 00:04:07,060
Furthermore,

85
00:04:07,240 --> 00:04:09,570
our exclusive mechanical purification
and extraction technology

86
00:04:09,590 --> 00:04:12,410
and advanced production
and sales management system

87
00:04:12,840 --> 00:04:14,380
will earn us no less than 20% of shares.

88
00:04:16,310 --> 00:04:18,580
Though I studied in the US

89
00:04:18,950 --> 00:04:21,020
and can vouch for what you claim,

90
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:24,370
given our unique national conditions,

91
00:04:24,680 --> 00:04:27,540
international practice isn't applicable.

92
00:04:27,870 --> 00:04:28,700
How so?

93
00:04:28,870 --> 00:04:30,930
Northeast China has fallen.

94
00:04:31,120 --> 00:04:33,930
Japanese is poised
to attack north China.

95
00:04:34,950 --> 00:04:36,020
In my opinion,

96
00:04:36,240 --> 00:04:38,650
a great war between China and Japan
is inevitable in two years.

97
00:04:39,120 --> 00:04:40,340
To build factories now

98
00:04:40,440 --> 00:04:42,530
is not only
to secure national livelihood

99
00:04:42,950 --> 00:04:45,130
but also to prepare for wars.

100
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:46,980
It's indeed imperative.

101
00:04:47,320 --> 00:04:49,250
But your collaboration terms strike us

102
00:04:49,550 --> 00:04:50,660
as excessively demanding.

103
00:04:52,960 --> 00:04:55,620
We have no choice.

104
00:04:56,040 --> 00:04:59,290
Our nation is at its weakest point,

105
00:04:59,560 --> 00:05:01,290
with finances
strained to breaking point.

106
00:05:01,680 --> 00:05:04,020
We earnestly request that Ms. Chu

107
00:05:04,920 --> 00:05:06,370
serve the country first

108
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:08,660
before pursuing personal gains.

109
00:05:09,360 --> 00:05:11,290
We should serve the country,

110
00:05:12,240 --> 00:05:15,370
yet the Miracle Pill
is the Chu family's treasure.

111
00:05:16,270 --> 00:05:17,610
If Ms. Chu simply hands it over,

112
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:20,170
she can't face her ancestors.

113
00:05:20,510 --> 00:05:21,140
Moreover,

114
00:05:21,630 --> 00:05:23,340
the success of the Miracle Pill today

115
00:05:23,630 --> 00:05:25,290
stems from her years of effort.

116
00:05:25,950 --> 00:05:26,580
If you

117
00:05:26,600 --> 00:05:28,050
show no regard for that,

118
00:05:28,750 --> 00:05:31,370
that would strike anyone as unfair.

119
00:05:35,720 --> 00:05:39,050
Then what terms do you propose?

120
00:05:40,390 --> 00:05:42,250
We demand at least 60% of shares.

121
00:05:42,480 --> 00:05:44,290
Only I and those I designated

122
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:47,980
can control the formula.

123
00:05:51,430 --> 00:05:53,410
The shares are negotiable,

124
00:05:54,240 --> 00:05:55,850
but the formula must be shared.

125
00:05:56,190 --> 00:05:57,340
No room for discussion on this.

126
00:05:57,750 --> 00:05:58,490
Ms. Chu,

127
00:05:59,190 --> 00:06:00,490
only by sharing the formula

128
00:06:00,750 --> 00:06:01,930
can we expedite factory construction,

129
00:06:01,950 --> 00:06:02,900
ramp up mass production,

130
00:06:03,120 --> 00:06:05,460
and meet the wartime needs.

131
00:06:09,310 --> 00:06:11,340
But as Mr. Cheng pointed out,

132
00:06:13,040 --> 00:06:15,490
this formula came from my ancestors.

133
00:06:16,830 --> 00:06:18,850
I cannot surrender it lightly.

134
00:06:22,510 --> 00:06:25,810
Things have gotten this bad

135
00:06:27,560 --> 00:06:28,900
mainly because

136
00:06:28,920 --> 00:06:31,980
so many cling to self-interest

137
00:06:32,510 --> 00:06:34,050
instead of serving the nation.

138
00:06:34,870 --> 00:06:36,050
I thought

139
00:06:36,240 --> 00:06:37,850
you were not like

140
00:06:38,680 --> 00:06:39,460
the rest.

141
00:06:43,510 --> 00:06:45,460
I'm leaving.

142
00:07:00,070 --> 00:07:01,370
If our nation ceases to exist,

143
00:07:03,070 --> 00:07:05,170
what's the use of keeping the formula?

144
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:08,810
But this isn't negotiation.

145
00:07:09,310 --> 00:07:10,100
It's outright robbery!

146
00:07:12,160 --> 00:07:13,370
Terms can be negotiated,

147
00:07:14,720 --> 00:07:16,610
but resisting Japanese aggression
admits no delay.

148
00:07:18,560 --> 00:07:19,170
Shaohua,

149
00:07:19,750 --> 00:07:21,140
you can serve our nation in many ways.

150
00:07:21,870 --> 00:07:23,540
Don't surrender what you own.

151
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:26,580
But I know

152
00:07:26,600 --> 00:07:28,540
many would gladly contribute every penny

153
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:31,700
they own to serve the nation,

154
00:07:32,920 --> 00:07:34,460
even giving up their lives.

155
00:07:36,040 --> 00:07:36,580
Alright.

156
00:07:37,360 --> 00:07:38,290
If you want,

157
00:07:38,950 --> 00:07:40,170
let it go to trustworthy hands.

158
00:07:41,040 --> 00:07:42,140
But the National Government…

159
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:46,170
If they commit to the resistance,

160
00:07:49,680 --> 00:07:51,100
I'll place my faith in them once.

161
00:07:51,720 --> 00:07:52,490
Mr. Ma.

162
00:07:55,310 --> 00:07:56,020
Ms. Chu.

163
00:07:57,040 --> 00:07:58,930
I can share the formula,

164
00:07:59,510 --> 00:08:01,050
but I have conditions.

165
00:08:01,480 --> 00:08:02,220
Please tell me.

166
00:08:03,040 --> 00:08:05,460
The Miracle Pill we produce

167
00:08:05,480 --> 00:08:07,220
will never be used for civil war,

168
00:08:07,360 --> 00:08:09,370
but only for those
resisting Japanese invaders.

169
00:08:09,600 --> 00:08:11,220
And all the profit,

170
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:12,340
including those allocated to me,

171
00:08:12,630 --> 00:08:14,290
will go to the war effort
resisting Japanese invaders.

172
00:08:15,510 --> 00:08:16,370
Excellent!

173
00:08:16,390 --> 00:08:17,540
No problem at all.

174
00:08:17,560 --> 00:08:19,460
Very well. As to details,

175
00:08:19,600 --> 00:08:21,290
please work them out together

176
00:08:21,310 --> 00:08:22,460
with Mr. Cheng.

177
00:08:23,390 --> 00:08:25,410
Thank you, Ms. Chu.

178
00:08:25,800 --> 00:08:26,580
Rest assured.

179
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:28,780
I'll never betray your trust

180
00:08:29,070 --> 00:08:30,170
and build factories without delay,

181
00:08:30,430 --> 00:08:32,580
to support the resistance against Japan.

182
00:08:33,030 --> 00:08:34,610
I await your good news.

183
00:08:34,630 --> 00:08:36,180
I'll do my best to hurry. See you.

184
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:45,530
Shaohua,

185
00:08:46,390 --> 00:08:47,700
you're suffering excessive losses.

186
00:08:48,600 --> 00:08:49,980
Facing the survival of the nation,

187
00:08:50,630 --> 00:08:51,850
personal interests

188
00:08:52,030 --> 00:08:53,250
pale into insignificance.

189
00:08:53,750 --> 00:08:55,730
But how will you face your ancestors?

190
00:08:55,910 --> 00:08:56,700
I believe

191
00:08:57,440 --> 00:08:59,010
they would support me.

192
00:09:00,270 --> 00:09:00,980
Let's go back.

193
00:09:08,360 --> 00:09:09,180
Mr. Xia,

194
00:09:10,600 --> 00:09:11,890
I'm willing to help you,

195
00:09:13,600 --> 00:09:14,610
but I don't need

196
00:09:16,440 --> 00:09:17,530
your money.

197
00:09:21,750 --> 00:09:22,340
Very well.

198
00:09:24,080 --> 00:09:25,340
Then let's hear your terms.

199
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:30,940
I wish to be your true friend.

200
00:09:32,440 --> 00:09:33,300
We've known

201
00:09:34,150 --> 00:09:35,700
each other for over 20 years.

202
00:09:36,120 --> 00:09:38,100
Aren't we true friends?

203
00:09:39,910 --> 00:09:41,460
Our previous connection

204
00:09:41,840 --> 00:09:44,220
was essentially transactional

205
00:09:44,390 --> 00:09:45,820
and mutual exchanges of interest.

206
00:09:47,270 --> 00:09:49,420
What I mean is friendship

207
00:09:49,510 --> 00:09:53,220
where souls intertwine

208
00:09:54,120 --> 00:09:55,220
and we share prosperity

209
00:09:55,440 --> 00:09:57,340
and suffering together.

210
00:09:57,910 --> 00:09:58,650
Do you understand?

211
00:10:01,510 --> 00:10:02,300
Well.

212
00:10:03,510 --> 00:10:04,730
What exactly is your point?

213
00:10:08,670 --> 00:10:10,300
I can have the Japanese Army

214
00:10:10,750 --> 00:10:14,100
return all your branches in northeast

215
00:10:14,120 --> 00:10:15,250
and north China to you,

216
00:10:15,840 --> 00:10:19,700
and help revive your sales
and supply chains.

217
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:21,890
But under one condition,

218
00:10:22,670 --> 00:10:25,130
we require 30% of shares

219
00:10:25,910 --> 00:10:27,530
in all those branches.

220
00:10:32,320 --> 00:10:34,730
Relax. You won't be treated unfairly.

221
00:10:35,360 --> 00:10:36,850
We'll purchase

222
00:10:37,480 --> 00:10:38,940
the 30% of shares

223
00:10:39,150 --> 00:10:40,580
at market value.

224
00:10:44,750 --> 00:10:45,890
This is important.

225
00:10:46,870 --> 00:10:47,820
Mr. Komura,

226
00:10:49,390 --> 00:10:50,820
please allow me to think thoroughly.

227
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:54,220
Besides,

228
00:10:54,240 --> 00:10:56,460
I have another request.

229
00:10:57,270 --> 00:10:57,940
Please say.

230
00:10:58,630 --> 00:11:00,490
Do you recall our last meeting?

231
00:11:01,480 --> 00:11:03,580
I asked for a few TCM formulas,

232
00:11:05,030 --> 00:11:06,420
yet you flatly rejected.

233
00:11:07,270 --> 00:11:08,010
This time,

234
00:11:09,750 --> 00:11:12,730
I hope you'll grant my wish.

235
00:11:15,150 --> 00:11:16,420
A few TCM formulas?

236
00:11:19,870 --> 00:11:20,940
Just one will do.

237
00:11:25,870 --> 00:11:26,890
You mean

238
00:11:29,150 --> 00:11:30,100
the Miracle Pill?

239
00:11:30,100 --> 00:11:32,070
[Jujing Apothecary]

240
00:11:33,480 --> 00:11:35,700
You mustn't agree.

241
00:11:36,150 --> 00:11:38,340
This is the only way
to save Shouyuan Apothecary!

242
00:11:40,120 --> 00:11:42,060
Even if we sacrifice the apothecary,

243
00:11:42,080 --> 00:11:44,370
we cannot let the Japanese
have their way!

244
00:11:44,790 --> 00:11:45,700
Nonsense.

245
00:11:45,720 --> 00:11:46,250
I…

246
00:11:46,750 --> 00:11:48,420
If Shouyuan Apothecary closes down,

247
00:11:48,670 --> 00:11:50,730
we'll lose most of our fortune.

248
00:11:51,030 --> 00:11:51,370
You…

249
00:11:51,390 --> 00:11:52,940
If Shouyuan Apothecary closes down,

250
00:11:54,030 --> 00:11:55,730
it'll be hard
to sustain Jujing Apothecary.

251
00:11:56,630 --> 00:11:58,580
Things will be worse than that.

252
00:12:00,910 --> 00:12:02,180
All our fortune will be gone.

253
00:12:03,080 --> 00:12:04,980
Then we must do something.

254
00:12:05,360 --> 00:12:08,730
The ancients never
compromised ethics for profit,

255
00:12:08,750 --> 00:12:10,220
or abandoned principles
when facing peril.

256
00:12:10,240 --> 00:12:12,980
We can't be worse than them.

257
00:12:16,550 --> 00:12:17,250
Have some water.

258
00:12:23,960 --> 00:12:24,730
Sandu,

259
00:12:26,360 --> 00:12:27,490
tell me what you think.

260
00:12:27,750 --> 00:12:28,980
When we did business

261
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:31,010
with the Japanese,

262
00:12:31,030 --> 00:12:32,220
we were criticized behind our backs

263
00:12:32,240 --> 00:12:33,610
by many people for years.

264
00:12:34,670 --> 00:12:36,580
You were removed as the Chairman

265
00:12:37,320 --> 00:12:38,490
of the TCM Guild for that.

266
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:40,010
These are two separate things.

267
00:12:40,720 --> 00:12:42,220
The removal was the doing

268
00:12:42,240 --> 00:12:44,850
of Mr. Tian and Wen Zhiqiu.

269
00:12:45,600 --> 00:12:48,100
If we let the Japanese invest now,

270
00:12:48,790 --> 00:12:50,940
we'll never rid ourselves of the label
of traitors.

271
00:12:51,510 --> 00:12:52,460
You know nothing.

272
00:12:52,790 --> 00:12:53,850
As the saying goes,

273
00:12:53,870 --> 00:12:55,980
a wise man adapts to the times.

274
00:12:56,320 --> 00:12:57,690
Of those we know,

275
00:12:58,750 --> 00:12:59,930
like Mr. Yang,

276
00:13:00,540 --> 00:13:02,210
he refused the Japanese investment,

277
00:13:02,350 --> 00:13:04,570
so he lost all his fortune overnight

278
00:13:04,590 --> 00:13:05,540
and died in poverty and illness.

279
00:13:05,830 --> 00:13:08,180
Whereas Liu Yutian is more adaptable,

280
00:13:08,400 --> 00:13:09,930
so he has made a fortune,

281
00:13:10,200 --> 00:13:11,660
and obtained a title of nobility.

282
00:13:11,920 --> 00:13:14,500
Don't be so short-sighted!

283
00:13:14,540 --> 00:13:16,260
If the three northeastern provinces
are restored,

284
00:13:16,400 --> 00:13:19,690
he is bound to meet a terrible end.

285
00:13:20,040 --> 00:13:20,810
Come on!

286
00:13:21,920 --> 00:13:23,930
The National Government is incapable!

287
00:13:24,830 --> 00:13:26,900
I doubt
if they can restore the fallen lands.

